subject: Pole Vault
lead_paragraph: Stacy Dragila, who dominated American women’s pole-vaulting for more than a decade, and Jenn Stuczynski, her successor, were matched Tuesday for the 101st Millrose Games on Feb. 1 in Madison Square Garden.Dragila, 36, is competing again after chronic Achilles’ tendon problems. In a two-week period last summer, Stuczynski broke Dragila’s American record of 15 feet 10 inches, then became the second woman in track and field history to clear 16 feet.
